statement_latex:
It costs a small firm C(q) dollars to produce q kilograms of a certain
chemical, where

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle{}C(q)=3q^{4/3}+50q+10000
\end{align*}

The average cost of production per kilogram is defined to be

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle{}\frac{C(q)}{q}.
\end{align*}

Use calculus to find how many kilograms the firm should produce in order
to minimize the average cost of production per kilogram. Please
simplify. You need not justify that your calculation actually minimizes
average cost.
